<p>
This September 23-26, the Indiana University Department of History and
Philosophy of Science will host a three day conference on "Integrated History
and Philosophy of Science." This is the third in a series of meetings devoted to
the topic, and it coincides with the fiftieth anniversary of the Indiana HPS
Department. The paper topics range from a discussion of seventeenth-century
comet theory to history and philosophy of contemporary embryology. For complete
information on the conference, including the program, abstracts of papers, and
details on lodging, go to <a href="http://www.indiana.edu/~andhps/" rel="external">http://www.indiana.edu/~andhps/</a>.
</p>
<p>
Please note that the block of hotel rooms reserved for the conference will be
released in mid-August. If you are planning to attend, we urge you to make your
booking as soon as possible.
